.TH YAML_FEED_INPUT 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_feed_input \- feed raw YAML text into a parser context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "size_t yaml_feed_input(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ", const uint8_t *" data ", size_t " len ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_feed_input ()
feeds raw YAML text bytes into a parser context. The parser processes
the input and enqueues events that can be dequeued with
.BR yaml_next_event (3).
.PP
For serializer contexts, this function stores the input for later use
in round-trip scenarios.
.PP
The function respects the
.I max_document_size
configuration limit. If the accumulated input exceeds this limit,
an error event is emitted and 0 is consumed.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of bytes consumed. Returns 0 if the input exceeds
.I max_document_size
or on error.
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_create (3),
.BR yaml_next_event (3),
.BR yaml_config_t (3)
